{"chunk_id": "a6b7d6a3-b3c8-4466-ab9b-8216ebb6a621", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 19, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "with the goals set in national policies on Agriculture, Health and Nutrition. The dietary guidelines ought to be practical, dynamic and flexible, based on the prevailing situation. Their utility is influenced by the extent to which they reflect the social, economic, agricultural and other environmental conditions. The guidelines can be considered as an integral component of the country's comprehensive plan to reach the goals specified in the National Nutrition Policy. The major food issues of concern are insufficient/ imbalanced intake of foods/nutrients. The common nutritional problems of public health importance in India are low birth weight, protein energy malnutrition in children, chronic energy deficiency in adults, micronutrient malnutrition and diet-related non- communicable", "embedding": [0.0034469543024897575, 0.037437062710523605, -0.021933505311608315, 0.04044824838638306, -0.009750576689839363, 0.06694557517766953, 0.008437380194664001, 0.0381937250494957, -0.10491309314966202, -0.09717945754528046, 0.059686269611120224, -0.06567049771547318, -0.03234205022454262, -0.08125481754541397, 0.02996017038822174, -0.06459792703390121, 0.12695108354091644, 0.010238556191325188, -0.079645074903965, -0.05804978683590889, 0.06413587182760239, 0.06472493708133698, 0.00995227973908186, -0.04320298507809639, -0.042373791337013245, -0.044425856322050095, 0.0885835811495781, -0.15411347150802612, -0.06744278967380524, 0.04499015584588051, 0.07647358626127243, -0.008079780265688896, 0.06371551752090454, -0.010990297421813011, -0.04973745346069336, 0.03834611922502518, 0.06346873939037323, -0.07096866518259048, -0.04883726313710213, -0.05949743464589119, -0.022931097075343132, -0.03241785988211632, -0.02379